</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,691,1869]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1807,1833]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[577,661,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otavalo">
<emphasis box="[577,661,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">otavalo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in reference to the canton and city Otavalo, as well as collection locality. It is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
